        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 7:56PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 756 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Castolon, or 19 miles southwest of Panther
Junction, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Panther Junction, Chisos Basin, and Big Bend National Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
